<image 1> On the basis of style, this work can be attributed to

A. Paul Cézanne
B. Claude Monet
C. José María Velasco
D. Vincent van Gogh

The style of the painting, characterized by its expressive brushwork, vivid colors, and emphasis on the emotional impact of the landscape, is indicative of the Post-Impressionist movement. Among the options provided, Vincent van Gogh is known for his Post-Impressionist works, which often feature such dynamic and expressive brushstrokes.

Therefore, the correct answer is:

D. Vincent van Gogh
